  "prompt": "What are the rules for Yahoo's fantasy hockey?",
  "response": "Yahoo Fantasy Hockey follows a standard set of rules that allow participants to manage their own virtual hockey team and compete against others. Here's an overview of the key rules and features:\n\n### 1. **League Setup**\n   - **League Types**: Public, Private, or Head-to-Head.\n   - **Draft Types**: Live Draft or Autodraft.\n   - **Team Rosters**: Typically include positions like Center (C), Left Wing (LW), Right Wing (RW), Defensemen (D), and Goalies (G).\n\n### 2. **Scoring**\n   - **Categories**: Points are awarded based on various statistical categories such as Goals (G), Assists (A), Plus/Minus (+/-), Penalty Minutes (PIM), Power-Play Points (PPP), Short-Handed Points (SHP), Shots on Goal (SOG), Wins (W), Goals Against Average (GAA), and Save Percentage (SV%).\n   - **Customization**: Leagues can customize scoring settings to emphasize different stats or to create unique league rules.\n\n### 3. **Roster Management**\n   - **Lineups**: Owners set weekly or daily lineups depending on league settings.\n   - **Player Adds/Drops**: Owners can add free agents and drop players from their roster throughout the season.\n   - **Trades**: Owners can propose and accept trades with other teams in the league.\n\n### 4. **Waivers and Free Agents**\n   - **Waiver Wire**: Players recently dropped by other teams go on waivers for a set period (e.g., 2 days) before becoming free agents.\n   - **Waiver Priority**: Determined by a priority system or a \"rolling list\" based on inverse order of standings.\n\n### 5. **Playoffs**\n   - **Format**: Typically follows a head-to-head format with teams competing in a playoff bracket.\n   - **Seeding**: Determined by regular-season standings.\n\n### 6. **Additional Features**\n   - **Commissioner Tools**: League commissioners can adjust settings, resolve disputes, and manage the league.\n   - **Mobile App**: Manage teams, set lineups, and follow scores on the go.\n   - **Message Boards**: Interact with other league members through discussions and trash-talk.\n\n### 7. **Player Eligibility**\n   - **Position Eligibility**: Players may be eligible at multiple positions based on their performance in the previous season.\n   - **Injuries/Suspensions**: Owners can place injured or suspended players on the Injured Reserve (IR) slot if available.\n\n### 8. **Matchups**\n   - **Weekly Matchups**: Teams compete head-to-head each week, with the winner determined by the total points or categories won.\n   - **Daily Matchups**: Some leagues may use a daily matchup format, where lineups are set daily.\n\nFor the most accurate and detailed rules, it's always a good idea to check the specific settings and rules of your Yahoo Fantasy Hockey league, as some features and settings can be customized by the league commissioner.",
